Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.71,0:00:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Convenience stores.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.48,0:00:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Staying open until late every day of the year,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.76,0:00:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,these shops sell food and daily necessities,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.73,0:00:15.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as providing various services.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.28,0:00:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what did today's culprit buy?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.67,0:00:22.53,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A canvas stained black with crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.53,0:00:25.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With brilliant detective skills, its color is changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.24,0:00:27.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Tales of first love were set aflame...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.12,0:00:29.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Uncover the arsonist's trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.33,0:00:31.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:33.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.01,0:00:35.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.58,0:02:18.24,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were invited to the birthday party of Asami Uchida,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:21.12,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}rumored to have been Shin'ichi's first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.12,0:02:26.58,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She fell asleep, so the rest of us went to the Karaoke Room in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.22,0:02:30.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's when one of her friends noticed the lodge was on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.86,0:02:35.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Asami Uchida was asleep in the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.49,0:02:42.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Luckily, Ran broke down the door\Nand managed to save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.70,0:02:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! She said that in her sleep?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.32,0:03:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I was saying, she was sleep-mumbling\Nwhen they brought her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.41,0:03:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm sorry! I'm sorry, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! I'm so sorry!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.79,0:03:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would she say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.25,0:03:16.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How should I know? That's just what I heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.35,0:03:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyways, are you thirsty?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.25,0:03:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can get you something from the vending machine downstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.80,0:03:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come with you, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.28,0:03:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.44,0:03:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! He's perfectly okay! Not a scratch on him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.23,0:03:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet he's with your dad, loitering around the scene of the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.87,0:03:57.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was it really an accident? Did they just forget to put out the candles?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.60,0:04:01.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so, then why was she asleep on the sofa when we left
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.88,0:04:05.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but on the floor during the fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.30,0:04:07.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And this room...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.01,0:04:12.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Something seems off about the furniture before and after the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.33,0:04:14.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Almost as if someone moved it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.83,0:04:18.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could it be?! Did someone come back here to set the fire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:22.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If so, then Morimoto{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} would be most suspicious, as he had the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.59,0:04:25.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:30.41,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Anyone could've easily entered via a window unlocked in advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.41,0:04:33.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Think! Think!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.49,0:04:37.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}According to the witnesses, the fire started around 2:50.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.50,0:04:41.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were all in the karaoke booth at 3:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.26,0:04:48.36,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}By car, it'd take five minutes to get here. Running, it'd take fifteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.36,0:04:50.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No one was gone for 30 minutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:54.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}so only Noguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} could've gone there, set the fire, and returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.21,0:04:56.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}since he had the car key...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:05:00.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The car was parked in front of the karaoke place,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.18,0:05:03.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and everyone left 30 minutes before to use the station bathrooms
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.18,0:05:06.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and buy cigarettes and such from the convenience store next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.27,0:05:09.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So someone would've noticed if the car was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.69,0:05:14.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If not the car... Chika{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s motorcycle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:19.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, it was parked in front of the lodge when we rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.67,0:05:21.14,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.14,0:05:25.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}None of the people in the karaoke booth could've done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:30.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It'd be a different story if there was a timer device of some sort,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.31,0:05:34.18,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but if there had been one, the firemen would've found it long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:39.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Which leaves what the old guy said...\NIt was Asami{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} who...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.65,0:05:40.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it, little boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:44.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know you shouldn't be in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.69,0:05:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.03,0:05:50.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah. I hear today's the birthday\Nof that girl who was asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.58,0:05:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The presents and the cake all burned up, but this survived the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.26,0:05:58.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a birthday message for her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:06:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go give it to her at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:02.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? They don't fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.26,0:06:05.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait a minute! Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:10.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come to think of it, that person did say something strange then!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.06,0:06:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh! Of course there was a fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.43,0:06:19.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cake with the lit candles was sitting on a chair!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.54,0:06:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mister. Was the cake really on a chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.94,0:06:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The chair was burnt up, and the cake turned to goop.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.59,0:06:29.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was this chair?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In front of that small, charred cabinet in the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.28,0:06:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But doesn't it seem strange to you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:47.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.76,0:06:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard she was in the tennis club until her 2nd year of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.00,0:06:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And she was the national champion that year!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.00,0:07:00.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? But wasn't she the soccer club manager in her 3rd year?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.53,0:07:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Apparently she completely changed after that summer break!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.76,0:07:06.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.15,0:07:10.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, anyways, she must've had her reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:12.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably none of our business to pry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.62,0:07:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wanna know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.23,0:07:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not so loud! You'll wake her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.90,0:07:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.48,0:07:20.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.90,0:07:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}S-Senpai{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.31,0:07:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Customers who came in at around 3:00?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Do you remember who came?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.24,0:07:38.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me think. Just some youngsters doing karaoke next door, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.13,0:07:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They bought cigarettes, tomato juice, and other stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.04,0:07:42.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were they like?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.14,0:07:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A brown-haired guy with glasses, a girl in a black dress,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.18,0:07:48.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and a guy with a buzz-cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.98,0:07:52.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sawai{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, Hayasaka{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}, and Noguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:07:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeesh! That buzz-cut guy puked in front of the store!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.81,0:07:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cleaning it up was such a pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.22,0:08:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Mister. Could you tell me if...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.88,0:08:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko! Any luck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.84,0:08:11.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she wasn't in the bathroom. How about you, Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.00,0:08:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No luck here, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} have gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.54,0:08:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just contact your dad for now! I'll go get a nurse!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.06,0:08:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.63,0:08:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right, little boy! How did you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.98,0:08:30.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him he had it backwards, but he didn't listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.44,0:08:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had sticky stuff on it, too. What a ridiculous customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.95,0:08:43.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No question about it! That person set the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.94,0:08:50.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And if my theory is right,\Nthe evidence is still in their possession!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.92,0:08:53.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disappeared?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious, Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.50,0:08:57.84,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah! She was in bed just a minute ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.84,0:09:01.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She must've left while we were getting something to drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.85,0:09:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do we do, Dad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.19,0:09:08.19,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Just look around outside the hospital!\NShe might still be nearby!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.19,0:09:09.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.{tune}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.69,0:09:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where could Asami have gone?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:16.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She may be planning to commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.60,0:09:17.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.28,0:09:23.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. If it really was Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who set the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.81,0:09:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or so one might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.29,0:09:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.20,0:09:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the truth is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:38.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was not the perpetrator but the victim!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.68,0:09:39.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Victim?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.72,0:09:44.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was nearly burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By one of you here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.63,0:09:57.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You can't be serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:10:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the fire started when we were in the karaoke booth!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd take 15 minutes to run from there to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.61,0:10:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or only five minutes by car or motorcycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.59,0:10:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car didn't seem to have been used,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.30,0:10:14.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the motorcycle was parked by this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.17,0:10:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of us could have come here to set the fire then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.87,0:10:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Though it'd be different if there was some sort of timer device,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.89,0:10:26.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but the firefighters would've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.69,0:10:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A timer device...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.85,0:10:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it was something not out of the ordinary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:36.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it was something that belonged there
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and could be controlled from a remote location?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.32,0:10:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. The perpetrator set the fire from kilometers away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.92,0:10:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using a certain thing at a certain location near the karaoke place!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.83,0:10:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Little boy! Everything's ready here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.26,0:11:00.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay! We'll be right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.38,0:11:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey. What's ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.81,0:11:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man asked me to have the firefighters set up the same trick
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:08.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that the bad guy used!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.90,0:11:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.79,0:11:12.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.51,0:11:16.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just such a surprisingly simple trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.70,0:11:18.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet it'll make you laugh, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. It's set up like the living room before the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It even has a fax machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.06,0:11:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.18,0:11:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how will this help?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:31.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pardon me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.04,0:11:34.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cake?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.97,0:11:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:40.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked Conan to buy some just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.32,0:11:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we place it on the chair in front of the fax machine, everything's set.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.54,0:11:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we just wait until it starts a fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhh, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.98,0:12:05.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not suggesting we wait until a candle falls to the floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.75,0:12:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, if that was what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.71,0:12:11.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that'd make it an accident caused by carelessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.19,0:12:12.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would hardly call...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.26,0:12:18.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.75,0:12:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's a fax!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.75,0:12:27.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:30.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That fax was sent by the convenience store owner at my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.66,0:12:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as the perpetrator sent one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.44,0:12:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.42,0:12:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's too simple!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.08,0:12:57.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the perpetrator's intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.85,0:13:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The more complicated the trick,\Nthe more likely evidence will be left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.20,0:13:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the idea was to simplify the trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.13,0:13:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,leave as little out of the ordinary as possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.17,0:13:12.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and make it look like an accidental fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.04,0:13:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.84,0:13:20.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You went to the convenience store to buy cigarettes at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.00,0:13:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...Manabu Sawai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.24,0:13:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You did it, Sawai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But he leapt into the flames to rescue Asami!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.95,0:13:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would he really rescue someone he was trying to kill?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.54,0:13:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, he was the first to notice the fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.22,0:13:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if he hadn't intended to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.18,0:13:46.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if this fire was set\Nso he could rescue Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.55,0:13:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped sedatives into her drink to make her sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.18,0:13:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,set up the trick just now while everyone was getting ready to leave,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then left the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To keep Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from burning to death, he placed her on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.75,0:14:05.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,far away from any furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, just as he planned, while everyone was busy doing karaoke,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.07,0:14:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he sent a fax to the lodge and started the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The store owner saw him sending the fax just before the fire started.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.23,0:14:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burned remnants of that fax were also found.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.55,0:14:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Burned remnants?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.89,0:14:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These! A firefighter gave them to me earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.01,0:14:35.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? The shapes don't fit, so there must've been two pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.78,0:14:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only one page was sent before the fire, so it seemed strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.01,0:14:41.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on, now! Yes, I did send a fax at the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.83,0:14:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was a fax I sent to a friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.81,0:14:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He asked me to come up with a good title for his novel!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:14:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh? A friend, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:15:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then how do you explain the transmit slip?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.40,0:15:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You gave the transmit slip to the store owner after you sent it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The date, time, phone number, and your fingerprints are on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.51,0:15:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's strange. I'm sure I sent it to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.04,0:15:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.45,0:15:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! I must've dialed the wrong number!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.93,0:15:32.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? My friend's number and this lodge's number are next to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.93,0:15:37.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, I'm president of Tohto University's mystery study club!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.18,0:15:40.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never use such an unreliable trick as that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.73,0:15:43.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you tested it with a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.30,0:15:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you set up the living room trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.85,0:15:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you used the fax machine's copy feature
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.28,0:15:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to determine where it would catch fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.68,0:15:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you know, to use the copy feature,\Nyou need to use an original.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.98,0:16:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you copied the birthday message Professor Takamura just sent,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.12,0:16:07.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,which was lying nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.35,0:16:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, you faxed that copy from the convenience store later.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.55,0:16:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The copy that had the message and cake cream on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.55,0:16:26.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner complained that you stuck sticky paper in the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.29,0:16:30.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He also said he told you it was backwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.88,0:16:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can't blame him.\NYou sent the blank side of the copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.20,0:16:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if two faxes with the same message were found at the scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.94,0:16:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would raise suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.14,0:16:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's enough! I'm sick of these groundless, made-up accusations!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're going to make such claims, show some proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.49,0:16:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you still playing innocent?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still have the fax in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People certainly are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.22,0:17:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They can't easily throw away anything that could put them in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.36,0:17:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They worry that someone else might pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're a prime example.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.64,0:17:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You even brought it back from the convenience store.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.29,0:17:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying he...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. He should still have it on him somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:28.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fax with Professor Takamura's message and cake cream on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.53,0:17:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you'll excuse us...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.84,0:17:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.87,0:17:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How ridiculous! I should've just thrown this thing away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.75,0:17:44.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then it really was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.73,0:17:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I set the fire. Using the exact method the detective explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:55.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know it was me? Anyone could've used that trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.96,0:17:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Think back to when we all rushed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.06,0:18:03.92,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Should we call her on the phone?!\NShe was asleep in the living room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.92,0:18:07.48,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's no use! It's already burned up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.71,0:18:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Only someone who knew where the fire was could've said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.96,0:18:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would you do that to Asami?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.44,0:18:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted her to love me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.44,0:18:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a brave man who risked his life\Nto rescue her from the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.58,0:18:29.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She turned me down when I asked her out last month.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.88,0:18:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That had never happened to me before, so I couldn't stand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.61,0:18:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd planned for it to be a small fire,\Nbut it spread faster than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.26,0:18:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.18,0:18:43.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a small fire?! It spread faster than you thought?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think those serve as excuses?! You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.65,0:18:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why couldn't you imagine Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} possibly burning to death?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.02,0:18:57.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The car could've gotten into an accident!\NIt could've gotten a flat tire!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.25,0:18:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There could've been a traffic jam!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.32,0:19:03.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would've lost her life\Nin any of those cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.62,0:19:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wanted her to love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:09.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,why didn't you consider becoming someone who could be loved?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.84,0:19:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you consider improving yourself instead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.46,0:19:19.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. That was very stupid, President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.25,0:19:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asami...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.91,0:19:23.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did something horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you did this for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.19,0:19:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright. You can explain everything to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.60,0:19:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,President.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.23,0:19:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't open people's hearts with force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.82,0:19:48.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.35,0:19:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet you could capture any man with a single breath, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.24,0:19:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.80,0:20:01.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just don't know about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.92,0:20:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Long ago, even I...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.99,0:20:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...even I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.23,0:21:31.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! You confessed to Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.60,0:21:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep. I was the one who confessed my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.92,0:21:37.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He completely rejected me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.01,0:21:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But the rumor said...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh. I started that rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.76,0:21:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really wanted him to like me.\NHe {\i1}was{\i0} my first love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.97,0:21:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he didn't seem to care about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.28,0:21:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm, there's one thing I'd like to know...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.58,0:21:58.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What exactly about him did you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.26,0:22:03.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm. I didn't really take notice of him at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.76,0:22:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his first year, he was a regular midfielder on the soccer team.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.51,0:22:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he was an impressive newcomer. That's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.76,0:22:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But one day, I shared some lemon pie I made with the soccer club.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.49,0:22:20.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone told me it was delicious, except for him...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.82,0:22:24.69,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? This is kind of bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.69,0:22:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi has a weird sense of taste!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.40,0:22:31.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. I guess it really wasn't very good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.56,0:22:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later on, everyone said they had pretended to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.72,0:22:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That hurt my feelings, so I baked a new one every day for 3 months
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.91,0:22:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,until he said it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.68,0:22:46.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, I was manager of the soccer club
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.12,0:22:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and fascinated with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.30,0:22:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone else made it great on her first try, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.36,0:22:57.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you know? I was mean and taught you a weird way of making it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.46,0:22:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?! How come?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.35,0:23:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh. Shall I tell you what he said after I confessed to him, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.82,0:23:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Umm, say...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.92,0:23:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pipe down! This is getting good! Be quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.78,0:23:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said this while acting embarrassed...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.58,0:23:20.15,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'm sorry, {\i1}senpai{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.15,0:23:24.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's someone I've been fond of since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.06,0:23:28.24,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}She's strong-minded and obstinate, yet easily moved to tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.24,0:23:30.44,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's that strangeness of hers...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.33,0:23:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.33,0:23:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hold on, Ran! Could that be...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.72,0:23:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you remember a girl like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.23,0:23:40.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.12,0:23:44.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh well.
